From 54e12bf6dc4dc07b272876f4689ba7a9434aa755 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Aug 2025 16:12:23 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi:ath12k: Fix stats timed out error in
 wmi control stats

Currently, when "echo 11 1 > ./sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/pci-0002:01:00.0
/mac0/wmi_ctrl_stats" is issued on the 6 GHz interface to fetch AFC stats,
the console logs a "wmi ctrl path stats timed out" error.

This occurs because ath12k_wmi_send_wmi_ctrl_stats_cmd() sends
WMI_REQUEST_CTRL_PATH_STATS_CMDID to firmware and waits for
WMI_CTRL_PATH_STATS_EVENTID. Upon receiving this event, the thread is
expected to post complete(&ar->debug.wmi_ctrl_path_stats_rcvd) to unblock
the wait.

However, ath12k_wmi_ctrl_path_stats_event() only processes
WMI_TAG_CTRL_PATH_PDEV_STATS and WMI_CTRL_PATH_PMLO_STATS, ignoring
WMI_CTRL_PATH_AFC_STATS. As a result, the event is freed via
ath12k_wmi_ctrl_path_stats_list_free() without posting the completion,
leading to a timeout.

Fix this by updating ath12k_wmi_ctrl_path_stats_event() to handle all
control stats types, including AFC. Also initialize src and dst pointers
for all stat types to ensure the WMI event is correctly copied to the ar
structure, preventing invalid pointer access.

Fixes: I673afada5a7 ("UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k:Datapath stats changes for ath12k unified driver framework part 2")
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
patches/ath12k/0009-wifi-ath12k-Add-WMI-control-path-stats-infra.patch

Change-Id: If7ca665ae4daa427a36e9e515a5f6f73932b8bd8
Signed-off-by: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c | 14 ++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
index 61a5d04f..faaaff93 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
@@ -13049,15 +13049,25 @@ static void ath12k_wmi_ctrl_path_stats_event(struct ath12k_base *ab, struct sk_b
 	stats = &ar->debug.wmi_ctrl_path_stats;
 	more = __le32_to_cpu(fixed_param->more);
 
+	src = &param.list;
+	dst = &stats->pdev_stats;
+
 	switch (tag_id) {
 	case WMI_TAG_CTRL_PATH_PDEV_STATS:
-		src = &param.list;
-		dst = &stats->pdev_stats;
 		break;
 	case WMI_CTRL_PATH_PMLO_STATS:
 		ath12k_dp_mon_pdev_update_telemetry_stats(ar->ab, ar->pdev_idx);
 		break;
+	case WMI_TAG_CTRL_PATH_STATS_EV_FIXED_PARAM:
+	case WMI_CTRL_PATH_CAL_STATS:
+	case WMI_CTRL_PATH_BTCOEX_STATS:
+	case WMI_CTRL_PATH_AWGN_STATS:
+	case WMI_CTRL_PATH_MEM_STATS:
+	case WMI_CTRL_PATH_AFC_STATS:
+		break;
+	/* Add case for newly wmi ctrl path added stats here */
 	default:
+		ath12k_warn(ab, "Received tag for wmi ctrl path stats %d\n", tag_id);
 		goto free;
 	}
 
